<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogger.Delete" Title="Delete method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogger">ILogger</PageRef> ->
    Delete
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>Delete</TypeRef> method destroys the logger object.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        Call this method only when manually managing a logger lifetime. In normal code, hold loggers in <TypeRef>ILogger::unique_ptr</TypeRef> and allow the custom deleter to call this method.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[virtual void Delete() = 0;]]></Code>
  </Section>
